06/02/2011
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The Sultanate of Oman has recognised Kosovo as an independent country, Deputy Foreign Minister Vlora Citaku confirmed on Friday (February 4th). 
The Gulf state became the 75th state to recognise Pristina's independence. 
Citaku said that Oman has sent a letter to Kosovo's embassy in London requesting the establishment of diplomatic relations. 
(RTS, Telegrafi, AFP - 04/02/11)
